<a class='reflink' href='../3.dcf/3.2.pi.html#theoremperppideals'>3.2.6</a>

<!-- 3.2.6 -->
<div class='toload theorem'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Theorem 3.2.6</span>
	Suppose $(X,\theta,\mathcal{A})$ is weakly regular.
	</p>
	
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li>
			For every $\perpp$-ideal $I$ of $\mathcal{A}$, $I=\mathbf{I}(\mathbf{U}(I))$.
		</li>
		
		<li>
			For every open subset $U\subseteq X$, $U=\mathbf{U}(\mathbf{I}(U))$.
		</li>
		
		<li>
			The map $U\mapsto\mathbf{I}(U)$ is an order isomorphism between the lattices of open sets of $X$ and $\perpp$-ideals of $\mathcal{A}$.
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>